1
00:00:05,423 --> 00:00:07,091
Wh-What?!

2
00:00:08,050 --> 00:00:12,471
Sera! Be my bride!

3
00:00:15,224 --> 00:00:19,395
A dream? Of the barbarian? But why?

4
00:00:23,399 --> 00:00:25,609
What is that sound?

5
00:00:53,929 --> 00:01:00,936
THE WARRIOR PRINCESS AND THE BARBARIC KING

6
00:02:13,676 --> 00:02:16,846
Wh-Wh-What are you doing in here?

7
00:02:17,471 --> 00:02:22,726
What are you asking? Why wouldn't
I be sleeping in my bedroom?

8
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:30,943
Why am I in your bedroom?!
And why are you nude?!

9
00:02:31,026 --> 00:02:33,195
You're making a real fuss
for how early it is.

10
00:02:33,279 --> 00:02:36,824
It's good to see you're so full
of energy, after last night.

11
00:02:40,494 --> 00:02:43,122
What happened last night...?

12
00:02:43,914 --> 00:02:46,542
I don't remember anything,
and I'm not sure I want to!

13
00:02:46,876 --> 00:02:51,922
Did you not just say you
wouldn't force yourself on me?

14
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:54,800
Come now, let's not quibble over details.

15
00:02:54,884 --> 00:02:58,470
Do not treat a lady's chastity
as some trifle, you animal!

16
00:02:58,554 --> 00:03:00,639
Wait, hold on.

17
00:03:01,265 --> 00:03:04,768
It's bad enough I've been
taken captive by barbarians...

18
00:03:04,852 --> 00:03:06,770
if I were to bear his child,

19
00:03:06,854 --> 00:03:09,148
I'd be giving rise to another
enemy to my homeland!

20
00:03:11,609 --> 00:03:13,402
Kill me! Now!

21
00:03:14,570 --> 00:03:16,280
What sense does that make?

22
00:03:17,114 --> 00:03:20,910
If you wanted to kill me,
I'd understand, but why seek to die?

23
00:03:22,161 --> 00:03:24,663
You would never understand.

24
00:03:24,955 --> 00:03:27,124
The shame of being defeated
and taken captive in battle...

25
00:03:27,207 --> 00:03:31,128
Compounded by the shame of attacking
a nude, unarmed opponent, in a rage...

26
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:33,547
All these things disgrace
a knight's honor!

27
00:03:34,006 --> 00:03:37,927
So, before I become any
greater of an embarrassment,

28
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:40,888
I would rather you put
me out of my misery!

29
00:03:40,930 --> 00:03:44,767
Well, that certainly sounds unpleasant.

30
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:47,353
U-Unpleasant?!

31
00:03:47,436 --> 00:03:49,521
How else would you describe your belief

32
00:03:49,605 --> 00:03:52,566
that shame and embarrassment are
enough to make one yearn for death?

33
00:03:52,775 --> 00:03:56,528
You make light of shame
and embarrassment?!

34
00:03:56,612 --> 00:03:58,822
These things may be of
no concern for you barbarians,

35
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:01,325
- but for a noble lady—
- Master Veor.

36
00:04:01,575 --> 00:04:03,786
Your clothes have dried.

37
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:08,207
You woke up with no trouble.
You're lucky.

38
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:09,708
What?

39
00:04:09,750 --> 00:04:12,753
After Master Veor returned yesterday...

40
00:04:15,965 --> 00:04:20,219
you had a mild overdose of the sleeping
drugs used to transport you here,

41
00:04:20,302 --> 00:04:23,472
so you suddenly started
vomiting, before collapsing.

42
00:04:24,264 --> 00:04:26,725
You had me quite worried.

43
00:04:27,142 --> 00:04:29,770
I collapsed? Then...

44
00:04:30,187 --> 00:04:34,024
That's what you meant about... last night.

45
00:04:34,233 --> 00:04:38,612
I should apologize. It was administered
in the same dosage that my people use.

46
00:04:38,696 --> 00:04:40,322
It's a type of paralytic poison,

47
00:04:40,406 --> 00:04:42,366
so you were brought to my
room so you could rest.

48
00:04:42,449 --> 00:04:44,034
Paralytic poison?!

49
00:04:44,118 --> 00:04:46,203
It slows the flow of blood,
which makes it good

50
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:48,080
for helping wounds close, as well.

51
00:04:48,872 --> 00:04:51,291
Then... nothing was done to me?

52
00:04:51,375 --> 00:04:54,378
Other than a misapplication
of medicine, no.

53
00:04:54,461 --> 00:04:57,589
I can't have you dying so soon
after I've decided to wed you!

54
00:04:58,424 --> 00:05:00,426
Don't be so confusing!

55
00:05:00,509 --> 00:05:03,012
Hand me a sword! I need
to beat some sense into you!

56
00:05:04,013 --> 00:05:06,473
Looks like I don't need
to worry about you.

57
00:05:07,016 --> 00:05:09,935
And the breakfast preparations
won't go to waste, either.

58
00:05:10,561 --> 00:05:11,895
Breakfast...?

59
00:05:11,937 --> 00:05:15,649
Yes. You haven't eaten anything in the
day since you left the battlefield.

60
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:16,942
I'd imagine you're hungry.

61
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:20,529
I'll be waiting in the other room,
so come along once you've calmed down.

62
00:05:20,612 --> 00:05:22,448
Hey—Wait!

63
00:05:28,495 --> 00:05:31,373
I can't believe that a
knight such as myself

64
00:05:31,457 --> 00:05:33,709
has been given shelter by barbarians...

65
00:05:35,335 --> 00:05:36,754
Grandfather.

66
00:05:36,837 --> 00:05:40,340
I taught you, my daughter,
my swordplay since you asked to learn,

67
00:05:40,424 --> 00:05:42,468
and you've proven to be
a bit too talented...

68
00:05:42,843 --> 00:05:44,344
Maybe if you were a man...

69
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:50,517
or could give up on being a knight...
you might've known some happiness.

70
00:05:51,226 --> 00:05:54,980
Serafina. You've rejected
another marriage proposal.

71
00:05:55,230 --> 00:05:56,940
Wanting to be a knight, as a woman...

72
00:05:57,024 --> 00:05:59,359
how long are you going to
indulge this selfishness?

73
00:05:59,651 --> 00:06:02,529
You've more than established yourself
as a leader of knights at this point.

74
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:05,282
You need to get married while
there are still viable prospects.

75
00:06:05,908 --> 00:06:07,993
A sword has never changed policy.

76
00:06:08,994 --> 00:06:10,204
Brother...

77
00:06:10,287 --> 00:06:13,916
I sensed a profound
sincerity from your blade.

78
00:06:14,291 --> 00:06:16,418
It was enough that I fell
for you in that moment.

79
00:06:17,836 --> 00:06:20,547
I've paid so little mind to my
femininity, the last thing I need

80
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:21,965
is to suddenly be desired for it!

81
00:06:22,049 --> 00:06:24,551
No... no, that isn't
the last thing I need.

82
00:06:25,010 --> 00:06:27,971
Considering he's a barbarian,
and I'm a prisoner of war...

83
00:06:28,055 --> 00:06:30,182
That is the entirety of the situation!

84
00:06:30,891 --> 00:06:36,647
And the breakfast for a prisoner of
war is likely to be the bare minimum.

85
00:06:36,730 --> 00:06:39,441
They say the best way to whittle one's
self-respect is through their diet.

86
00:06:40,442 --> 00:06:42,319
But as a knight, I've dealt
with military rations,

87
00:06:42,402 --> 00:06:44,613
so I doubt they can do much worse.

88
00:06:44,696 --> 00:06:47,950
I will display the pride of
the Lavillant clan that was

89
00:06:48,158 --> 00:06:50,577
chosen to be part of
the Eastern Expedition!

90
00:06:50,661 --> 00:06:52,454
There you are, Sera.

91
00:06:53,705 --> 00:06:55,290
Come, have a seat.

92
00:06:55,958 --> 00:06:58,252
There's meat!

93
00:06:58,585 --> 00:07:03,632
Where did this fatty meat come from?
Even at home, something like this...

94
00:07:03,715 --> 00:07:08,804
No, given the state of my homeland,
I never came across such a feast!

95
00:07:08,887 --> 00:07:12,307
I'm not sure what a good portion would
be for a female warrior from the west,

96
00:07:12,391 --> 00:07:14,935
but I'm sure a quarter should suffice.

97
00:07:16,603 --> 00:07:20,023
This is a quarter?!
It's bigger than my torso!

98
00:07:20,107 --> 00:07:23,944
What is this? Why would they
possibly be treating me like this?!

99
00:07:24,027 --> 00:07:26,071
What's the matter? Not hungry?

100
00:07:26,155 --> 00:07:29,575
I see. Your scheme is obvious, now.

101
00:07:30,492 --> 00:07:33,662
Foisting such luxury on me to
winnow away at my knight's pride,

102
00:07:33,745 --> 00:07:36,748
so that you might tame me, is that it?

103
00:07:37,875 --> 00:07:42,629
No matter! I would rather starve to
death than be indulged by barbarians!

104
00:07:45,424 --> 00:07:48,760
Did my stomach really need to
rumble at that exact moment?!

105
00:07:49,136 --> 00:07:51,013
K-Kill me!

106
00:07:51,096 --> 00:07:53,348
Are you fond of saying that?

107
00:07:53,432 --> 00:07:57,060
If your stomach still yearns for food,
it means your body wishes to go on living.

108
00:07:57,144 --> 00:08:01,982
To not eat, in spite of that,
is nothing more than self-deception.

109
00:08:02,065 --> 00:08:04,234
To say nothing of the disrespect
for the life that was lost

110
00:08:04,318 --> 00:08:05,819
so this food could be brought to you.

111
00:08:05,903 --> 00:08:09,781
Taking a life should be a serious
matter, not done out of sport.

112
00:08:10,032 --> 00:08:12,993
Surely, the west isn't so
different in what they believe.

113
00:08:14,536 --> 00:08:18,373
All that aside, stop second-guessing
everything and eat.

114
00:08:18,457 --> 00:08:19,541
It's good!

115
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:22,252
That smile...

116
00:08:25,255 --> 00:08:27,174
What is it, odd eyes?

117
00:08:27,257 --> 00:08:28,675
I should inform you...

118
00:08:29,718 --> 00:08:32,888
Though Master Veor didn't mention it,
given he took the fact for granted,

119
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:37,059
this meat was hunted
specifically to welcome you.

120
00:08:37,142 --> 00:08:38,685
A welcome?

121
00:08:39,770 --> 00:08:42,064
On a hunt he went on, by himself,

122
00:08:42,147 --> 00:08:46,193
so that you would have something
fine to eat upon waking.

123
00:08:46,443 --> 00:08:49,196
Master Veor is as capable
as he is famous...

124
00:08:49,279 --> 00:08:51,865
He would be the equivalent of
one of your western royalty.

125
00:08:51,949 --> 00:08:56,036
I mean, if he's the son of some great
chief... that would make him a prince.

126
00:08:56,119 --> 00:09:01,208
Someone like that went to a lot of
effort to show you this hospitality.

127
00:09:01,291 --> 00:09:04,461
Would turning away from it not
be bad manners for a noble?

128
00:09:07,923 --> 00:09:12,761
Fine. It would bring shame to my name
as a knight to reject such efforts.

129
00:09:14,930 --> 00:09:18,725
But if this is some paltry... so tender...

130
00:09:26,817 --> 00:09:29,361
So good!

131
00:09:29,444 --> 00:09:32,447
It's so tender, but so juicy!

132
00:09:32,531 --> 00:09:34,116
There's a bit of gaminess,

133
00:09:34,199 --> 00:09:37,744
but the flavor is good enough,
it comes across as a slight accent!

134
00:09:37,828 --> 00:09:41,707
I doubt even Illdoren royalty
get to eat something like this!

135
00:09:41,748 --> 00:09:45,252
Glorious... too glorious!

136
00:09:45,502 --> 00:09:47,462
Well? Good, isn't it?

137
00:09:48,588 --> 00:09:53,260
Well, I can hardly complain after
being served something like this.

138
00:09:53,468 --> 00:09:56,138
And while I don't intend on marrying you,

139
00:09:56,221 --> 00:09:58,932
this is enough for me to overlook
the matter of my drugging.

140
00:10:00,058 --> 00:10:01,768
That's good, then.

141
00:10:02,144 --> 00:10:05,772
I have to ask, as good as it tastes,
what manner of meat is this?

142
00:10:06,023 --> 00:10:07,107
Care to see?

143
00:10:07,691 --> 00:10:10,610
It was bled and the organs were
removed up in the mountains,

144
00:10:11,236 --> 00:10:13,530
but the rest is being cleaned out back.

145
00:10:13,739 --> 00:10:16,658
If you're curious, you can
look from that window.

146
00:10:17,784 --> 00:10:19,536
I want to know!

147
00:10:19,619 --> 00:10:23,665
If we could domesticate this animal
in my homeland, then maybe...

148
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:27,377
There's no shortage of
them in these parts.

149
00:10:30,464 --> 00:10:32,591
It's called a dragon.

150
00:10:32,674 --> 00:10:36,386
A-A dragon?!

151
00:10:36,470 --> 00:10:39,639
Th-This is dragon meat?!

152
00:10:39,723 --> 00:10:40,724
Yes.

153
00:10:41,641 --> 00:10:44,061
As in... the legendary...

154
00:10:44,269 --> 00:10:46,438
flying monster?!

155
00:10:46,521 --> 00:10:48,648
That's apparently how
they're viewed in the west.

156
00:10:48,732 --> 00:10:53,403
They're supposed to breathe
fire and have toxic flesh!

157
00:10:53,487 --> 00:10:56,281
Those do exist, but this
is a different breed.

158
00:10:57,783 --> 00:11:04,790
That aside, Sera, I notice
you're... not slowing down.

159
00:11:04,998 --> 00:11:08,585
Well, if it tastes good, it tastes good.

160
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:16,676
I don't think she intends
on dying any time soon.

161
00:11:19,721 --> 00:11:22,557
I'm allowed to go outside?

162
00:11:22,641 --> 00:11:26,478
Yes. There's something around the
mountain I'd like to show you.

163
00:11:27,938 --> 00:11:31,691
What? You look like the dragon
that swallowed a wasp's nest.

164
00:11:31,775 --> 00:11:36,029
Obviously I can't just trust
you about something like that.

165
00:11:36,738 --> 00:11:37,823
It's a matter of trust?

166
00:11:37,906 --> 00:11:41,368
Of course it is! I've only been
your prisoner for two days!

167
00:11:41,451 --> 00:11:44,329
Not that the length of
time matters, but...

168
00:11:44,413 --> 00:11:46,873
Besides, it doesn't make sense,

169
00:11:46,957 --> 00:11:49,334
waltzing around lands filled
with such bizarre creatures!

170
00:11:49,418 --> 00:11:54,423
You speak of sense, but surely common
sense varies depending on location.

171
00:11:54,506 --> 00:11:57,926
I'd say different creatures and
cultures are a big part of that.

172
00:11:58,009 --> 00:12:01,012
Or is it simply that you're afraid?

173
00:12:03,765 --> 00:12:09,062
I can't deny that you've
baited me into this...

174
00:12:09,146 --> 00:12:11,440
But don't get the wrong idea.

175
00:12:11,523 --> 00:12:14,901
This doesn't mean I trust you people.

176
00:12:14,985 --> 00:12:19,156
Obviously. Still, I get the feeling
you'll take a liking to your surroundings,

177
00:12:19,239 --> 00:12:20,657
once you've seen them.

178
00:12:21,408 --> 00:12:22,784
And what are you basing that on?

179
00:12:22,868 --> 00:12:26,413
There's no basis.
It's just a gut feeling, that's all.

180
00:12:53,815 --> 00:12:55,525
Something wrong?

181
00:12:55,942 --> 00:13:02,199
No... it's just... more bountiful,
and richer in nature than I had imagined.

182
00:13:02,282 --> 00:13:05,160
The battlefields we fought
on were wastelands,

183
00:13:05,744 --> 00:13:08,580
but the life in these lands
has always been strong.

184
00:13:08,955 --> 00:13:11,249
I just hope you don't faint from it all.

185
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:13,627
D-Don't mock me!

186
00:13:14,961 --> 00:13:19,424
Damned barbarian. The dragon and this
scenery were basically sneak attacks.

187
00:13:19,508 --> 00:13:21,468
I don't know what he
intends on showing me,

188
00:13:21,551 --> 00:13:24,763
but if I can brace for it,
I won't be surprised.

189
00:13:37,192 --> 00:13:39,069
So many animals...

190
00:13:41,196 --> 00:13:44,783
Dragons are just another one of
the inhabitants of these parts.

191
00:13:44,866 --> 00:13:46,535
They're a pain to hunt,

192
00:13:46,618 --> 00:13:50,247
but if you leave their lairs alone,
they don't bother humans.

193
00:13:50,622 --> 00:13:53,333
You make it sound so
simple to get used to!

194
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:55,585
It will be, once you live here.

195
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:59,631
You certainly seemed to enjoy
the one you ate this morning.

196
00:14:00,465 --> 00:14:03,301
M-My meat wasn't flying...

197
00:14:04,177 --> 00:14:06,304
It's no different than poultry, then.

198
00:14:10,267 --> 00:14:11,810
What is that sound?

199
00:14:19,025 --> 00:14:23,029
Is that... a waterfall?!
I've never seen one before!

200
00:14:23,280 --> 00:14:26,908
What do you think, Sera?
Not a sight you'd see in the west.

201
00:14:26,992 --> 00:14:31,037
Are you mocking me?
My homeland has its own...

202
00:14:33,665 --> 00:14:36,001
No. It doesn't.

203
00:14:39,254 --> 00:14:42,215
I wasn't trying to brag, mind you.

204
00:14:42,299 --> 00:14:46,803
But I did want you to see it.

205
00:14:48,054 --> 00:14:51,558
Now, then, there's one other
thing that brings us here.

206
00:14:51,808 --> 00:14:54,144
- There is?
- Yes.

207
00:14:54,227 --> 00:14:57,022
First of all... strip.

208
00:14:58,106 --> 00:14:59,858
Wh-Why would I?!

209
00:14:59,941 --> 00:15:00,942
You ask why?

210
00:15:01,276 --> 00:15:03,737
There's only one thing a man and
woman would do in the water,

211
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:04,863
without their clothes.

212
00:15:05,864 --> 00:15:07,949
D-Don't tell me...

213
00:15:08,241 --> 00:15:09,284
Bathe.

214
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:11,786
Do you have to say everything
in such a misleading way?!

215
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:13,705
Even if I'm getting used to it!

216
00:15:14,247 --> 00:15:18,251
Besides, why would you have
mixed bathing?! It's indecent!

217
00:15:18,335 --> 00:15:22,339
You can call it indecent, but that's
simply how it's done around here.

218
00:15:22,422 --> 00:15:25,467
Don't they say "When in foreign lands,
do as the foreigners do"?

219
00:15:26,343 --> 00:15:29,638
I'm not going to engage with
your barbarian practices!

220
00:15:29,721 --> 00:15:31,556
My, you're a fierce one.

221
00:15:32,432 --> 00:15:34,059
You're beginning to smell a bit.

222
00:15:34,726 --> 00:15:37,937
We don't have bathhouses in our culture.

223
00:15:38,063 --> 00:15:40,690
Wiping you down like
last night can only do so much.

224
00:15:40,774 --> 00:15:42,984
It won't be long before
you start to stink...

225
00:15:45,695 --> 00:15:47,989
I can't believe you, either.

226
00:15:48,657 --> 00:15:51,576
Taking your clothes off with no
hesitation, in front of a man...

227
00:15:51,660 --> 00:15:54,621
On some level, it's just a
matter of being used to it.

228
00:15:54,954 --> 00:15:57,290
Master Veor even went
to a different stream

229
00:15:57,374 --> 00:15:59,042
because of the fuss you were making.

230
00:15:59,125 --> 00:16:01,878
So, I'm here to accompany you.

231
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:04,923
More like watch me, so I can't run.

232
00:16:05,465 --> 00:16:10,220
No, I'd say it has more to
do with keeping you safe.

233
00:16:10,303 --> 00:16:11,930
My safety?

234
00:16:14,641 --> 00:16:17,602
There are other things out
here, like the sawaiwao.

235
00:16:18,687 --> 00:16:21,272
- See?
- Don't you "see?" me!

236
00:16:22,065 --> 00:16:26,277
Well, they're all pretty docile
if they can be found here.

237
00:16:26,569 --> 00:16:30,740
You make it sound like we're
surrounded by monsters or something.

238
00:16:30,824 --> 00:16:32,534
Because we are.

239
00:16:42,669 --> 00:16:45,422
How can I bathe while
surrounded by monsters?!

240
00:16:45,463 --> 00:16:47,298
I'm going back!

241
00:16:47,382 --> 00:16:48,925
But that's...

242
00:16:50,593 --> 00:16:52,429
Well, I guess it'll be fine.

243
00:16:56,474 --> 00:16:59,352
I ran off without thinking...

244
00:16:59,936 --> 00:17:03,857
But it was careless to leave my shoes
and clothes in the other direction.

245
00:17:06,609 --> 00:17:09,654
I'm not happy about it, but I
suppose I'll head back and get dressed.

246
00:17:09,738 --> 00:17:10,947
Is someone there?

247
00:17:12,407 --> 00:17:15,076
Oh, no! Someone else is out here!

248
00:17:17,328 --> 00:17:18,538
Kill me!

249
00:17:19,164 --> 00:17:21,666
What'll happen if I run
into a real savage,

250
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:24,961
unlike the strangely rational Veor?!

251
00:17:28,923 --> 00:17:31,092
S-Stay back!

252
00:17:37,599 --> 00:17:39,726
What are you doing here?

253
00:17:40,643 --> 00:17:42,562
S-So handsome!

254
00:17:42,645 --> 00:17:46,316
A young barbarian warrior?
And one that's so beautiful!

255
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:49,652
I'm hard-pressed to think of many
men in the west who look so...

256
00:17:49,736 --> 00:17:53,615
Y-You! Stop staring!

257
00:17:54,199 --> 00:17:56,075
From the state of you...

258
00:17:56,159 --> 00:17:58,870
I'd guess some beasts appeared while
you were bathing in the falls.

259
00:18:00,622 --> 00:18:03,291
My mother was a warrior
from the west, too.

260
00:18:03,374 --> 00:18:06,252
I've heard stories like that.

261
00:18:06,336 --> 00:18:09,214
She would tell me, when I was young,

262
00:18:09,297 --> 00:18:13,885
about how there was less nature and
fewer animals where she came from.

263
00:18:14,135 --> 00:18:17,806
From his age, that'd have to have
been in the 16th Expedition...

264
00:18:17,889 --> 00:18:20,809
A lady knight from 20
years ago is his mother?

265
00:18:23,019 --> 00:18:25,605
Damn, I'm actually getting cold.

266
00:18:31,027 --> 00:18:32,654
Wh-What are you doing?

267
00:18:32,737 --> 00:18:36,032
Honestly, a woman shouldn't
risk catching a chill.

268
00:18:37,617 --> 00:18:40,286
Let's head back to where your clothes are.

269
00:18:40,370 --> 00:18:42,914
You can use my coat in the meantime.

270
00:18:43,164 --> 00:18:44,415
What a gentleman!

271
00:18:45,166 --> 00:18:48,878
What is a man who could be a western
knight doing among these barbarians?!

272
00:18:48,962 --> 00:18:52,257
Or is it just Veor, whose first
words to me were about marriage,

273
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:53,800
that is abnormal?

274
00:18:55,844 --> 00:18:57,011
Are you all right?

275
00:18:59,013 --> 00:19:00,390
Do you have a fever?

276
00:19:00,473 --> 00:19:02,892
- Too close! His face is too close!
- You're turning red, too.

277
00:19:02,934 --> 00:19:07,689
Not good! I don't have enough experience
with men to know what to do!

278
00:19:08,606 --> 00:19:10,400
This isn't good.

279
00:19:10,483 --> 00:19:12,819
You might have trouble making it
down the mountain.

280
00:19:13,069 --> 00:19:16,197
So be it. I'll have to
touch you, so forgive me.

281
00:19:16,489 --> 00:19:17,574
Wha...?

282
00:19:23,663 --> 00:19:26,207
You're as light as a feather.

283
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:28,209
What am I supposed to do here?

284
00:19:28,293 --> 00:19:31,462
Even I'm shocked at how
little resistance I can muster...

285
00:19:31,504 --> 00:19:33,423
Okay, let's go.

286
00:19:33,464 --> 00:19:36,467
Oh, I finally found you.

287
00:19:37,135 --> 00:19:40,597
Sorry to ruin what seems
like a nice moment,

288
00:19:40,889 --> 00:19:44,100
but how did this even happen,

289
00:19:44,309 --> 00:19:45,894
Master Veor?

290
00:19:47,228 --> 00:19:48,229
Ve...

291
00:19:48,313 --> 00:19:50,982
What, you didn't realize?

292
00:19:51,190 --> 00:19:54,152
I suppose I didn't get to tidy
myself up before proposing, but...

293
00:19:57,989 --> 00:20:01,743
All it took was a shave for
you to blush like a maiden.

294
00:20:02,535 --> 00:20:04,495
You're an innocent one, aren't you?

295
00:20:07,749 --> 00:20:10,585
I am a maiden, you barbarian!

296
00:20:13,421 --> 00:20:15,924
To slap with such force
from an unstable position.

297
00:20:16,049 --> 00:20:18,760
I knew I liked you for a reason.

298
00:20:19,052 --> 00:20:22,472
You're bright red.
Are you going to be all right?

299
00:20:25,058 --> 00:20:27,936
If I had a sword, it would've
been grounds for a duel!

300
00:20:28,019 --> 00:20:32,732
Besides, this is your fault for
taking me into that den of monsters.

301
00:20:32,815 --> 00:20:36,569
- You didn't need to worry about that.
- Huh?

302
00:20:36,653 --> 00:20:41,407
Master Veor patrols the areas where
dangerous creatures might appear.

303
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:45,703
You didn't seem to want any
company while in the nude.

304
00:20:45,787 --> 00:20:48,164
I had intended on protecting you
by your side, at first, but...

305
00:20:48,414 --> 00:20:50,708
Compared to the yoitobari
we had for breakfast,

306
00:20:50,792 --> 00:20:53,670
the inhabitants of the
river are all peaceful.

307
00:20:53,753 --> 00:20:56,881
W-Was that dragon that dangerous?

308
00:20:56,923 --> 00:20:58,758
I wouldn't say so.

309
00:20:58,841 --> 00:21:02,053
They have a wild temper,
but are generally pretty cowardly.

310
00:21:02,345 --> 00:21:04,847
Only you would say that, Master Veor.

311
00:21:04,931 --> 00:21:09,686
Even if they are herbivores, a dragon of
that size is a danger for most people.

312
00:21:09,727 --> 00:21:11,813
I can't argue with that, but...

313
00:21:13,064 --> 00:21:16,526
I got to see another side
of the woman I love today.

314
00:21:16,609 --> 00:21:19,195
It was a small price to pay, frankly.

315
00:21:20,071 --> 00:21:22,782
I will forgive you, this one time!

316
00:21:22,865 --> 00:21:25,410
On account of how nice the scenery was.

317
00:21:26,202 --> 00:21:28,204
But it won't happen again!

318
00:21:28,579 --> 00:21:30,415
That's fine by me!

319
00:21:30,498 --> 00:21:34,335
It's a relief to know how
gracious my wife is, as well.

320
00:21:34,419 --> 00:21:37,547
Wi—?! You don't get to
decide that I'm your wife!

321
00:21:37,630 --> 00:21:39,424
Really? Still?

322
00:21:39,507 --> 00:21:41,217
Don't give me that look full of pity!

323
00:21:41,634 --> 00:21:43,177
Unbelievable...

324
00:21:46,389 --> 00:21:50,351
What an absolute mess. Although...

325
00:21:51,894 --> 00:21:57,900
I suppose he's easier
on the eyes without that beard.

326
00:21:58,359 --> 00:22:00,611
Only slightly, though!

327
00:22:04,741 --> 00:22:06,701
DAYS LATER

328
00:22:07,869 --> 00:22:08,953
But...

329
00:22:12,373 --> 00:22:13,541
Why?
